The Hodge Conjecture is one of the seven Millennium Prize Problems, and it's a fundamental open problem in algebraic geometry. It relates the topology of complex algebraic varieties to their algebraic structure. The conjecture states that for a non-singular complex projective variety, every Hodge class is a rational linear combination of classes of algebraic cycles.

